\par 1.3.0 March 8, 2006}{\f4\insrsid1385954 
\par 
\par   }{\i\f38\insrsid1385954 New Features:
\par    }{\f4\insrsid1385954 * A new \lquote status\rquote  report window. Displays hex, heading, speed, heat, status (destroyed/fallen/etc) and weapon/ammo information 
\par    * Armor/internal diagrams can be superimposed on tactical map. Must be activated under \lquote Map\rquote  menu [based on patch by Peitao Ting]
\par    * Support for loading/saving maps. From the File menu, if you select \lquote Load Map\rquote 
, Thud will attempt to load terrain information from that file. Thud will also automatically update that file every 5 minutes with new map information. If your unit changes maps, that is detected and auto-saving is stopped (so as not to overwrite \'93good
\'94 (RS) map information with \'93bad\'94 (hangar) map information).
\par    * Thud now automatically detects when you enter/exit mechs and suspends/resumes operation accordingly. The \lquote Start/Stop HUD\rquote  button (Ctrl-G) still works \endash 
 Thud will not automatically activate if the HUD has been stopped by a user (or not started yet)
\par    * Cliff detection is now done per-vehicle type \endash  if you\rquote re in a vehicle, the cliff lines will change (automatically) to show on 2 z difference instead of 3.
\par    * All windows can be made \'93always on top\'94 via preferences
\par    * The font size of the status bar at the bottom of the tactical window can now be configured via preferences.
\par    * The amount of time old contacts should be kept around can now be configured via preferences.
\par    * A new Window menu that can be used to restore accidentally-closed windows.
\par    }{\i\f38\insrsid1385954 
\par   Bug Fixes:
\par }{\f4\insrsid1385954    * The tactical display will reload quicker when you first start the HUD or when you change units.
\par    * Enemy contacts no longer in LOS now change color properly.
\par    * Disconnections are now handled much more gracefully (CPU no longer spikes, can\rquote t send commands)
\par    * Closing the main window of Thud now gracefully exits the whole program
\par    * Disconnecting from a MUX closes all windows except the main one
\par    * Airborne/quad unit arcs are now displayed correctly.
\par    * Changing the contacts window font size no longer changes the main window font size
\par 
